{"TopicId":217980,"ForumId":200,"TopicTitle":"FPS tanking when full KSC mesh is in view","CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T18:01:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T18:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7 10700K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX2060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe more of it is visible in the camera view, the less frames I have (it went as low as 2fps at one time), until very far when the framerate starts to come back. Both in flight and in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E view. See video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy settings are in attachment, and what seems to cause it is \u003Cstrong\u003ETexture Quality\u003C/strong\u003E set to \u003Cstrong\u003EHigh\u003C/strong\u003E.\u00A0 Normally, close on Kerbin ground I have around 30fps, it\u0027s just the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E that drops it. Any other settings look smooth there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is it may be a LOD issue? When it doesn\u0027t go to lower level when it should because it\u0027s not needed at larger distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220230624191325_1.jpg.3679ff7af3fd40a9d9532e7372cecd5e.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_06/20230624191325_1.jpg.3679ff7af3fd40a9d9532e7372cecd5e.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=framd.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BH3NoeWMvi12PFnyuqZUL3UBzz8p8WhvLWPBuYJMoiZK5x7bwlHp4SwBlF1bM4NgEYDvQyRzm13qzQT59Ihc=%5D%5Bd83b0fa644295045e8f45c72%5D%5B7a9b0488ebb4d8d82e148fce4c73d314%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eframd.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-09T08:54:56Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2023 08:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T19:18:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can confirm, even if I have a much more acceptable drop: 60fps to 40fps\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/f4YYrFx\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/f4YYrFx\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(video a bit blurry)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-24T19:18:53Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2023 07:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GANR1277","CreatedById":229540,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-29T18:46:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the same issue. If you teleport your ship to orbit, the FPS will tank above \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and exactly in the opposite side of Kerbin.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe fix:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you wish to flight without lagging, quicksave and quickload in launchpad before launch. Usually it works at first try. If not, repeat until you notice the framerate doesn\u0027t drop too much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}